'''Golan Space Defense Platforms''' (''GSDP's'') were a series of armed [[Space station/Legends|space stations]] built by [[Golan Arms/Legends|Golan Arms]]. They were considerably more powerful and more heavily defended than [[XQ Platform series|XQ Platforms]].

Designed for the defense of valuable [[Planet/Legends|planets]] and facilities, the [[Golan I Space Defense Platform/Legends|first Golan platforms]] began production during the closing [[Standard year/Legends|years]] of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]]. After the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] spurred the production of ever larger [[Warship/Legends|warships]], the original Golan SpaceGun was succeeded by the [[Golan II Space Defense SpaceGun]] and the [[Golan III Space Defense NovaGun]]. Later models included the [[Golan VIII space defense platform|Golan VIII]], which was fitted with a [[Hyperdrive/Legends|hyperdrive]] should the platform need to be relocated.

Golan platforms saw action in many notable battles from the [[Time/Legends|time]] of the Clone Wars through the rise of the [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances]], such as the [[Battle of Duro (Clone Wars)|Battle of Duro]] and the [[Battle of Bilbringi (9 ABY)|Battle of Bilbringi]].

Several Golan IIIs defended [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] during the [[Battle of Coruscant (Yuuzhan Vong War)|battle over it]] during the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]]. They formed the second tier of Coruscant's four tier defense system. After the fall of Coruscant, the Yuuzhan Vong pushed at least one of the platforms out of [[Orbit/Legends|orbit]] to crash on the planet's surface, as recorded by [[Tam Elgrin]].

Over a [[Standard century/Legends|hundred years]] later, the Golan VIII space defense platform would be used by the [[Galactic Alliance Remnant]].

